					<head>Halakhah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>A collection of halakhic works by various authors.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1v" to="129r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Sefer Or zaruʻa be-kitsur</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר אור זרוע בקיצור</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en">Ḥayim ben Isaac ben Moses, of Vienna</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he">חיים יצחק בן משה, מוינה</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>An abridgment of Sefer Or zaruʻa of Isaac ben Moses of Vienna, by his son Ḥayim.</p>
								<p>This recension differs in many instances from the printed editions.</p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="illustration">
								<locus n="128r"/>A drawing of a hybrid creature, in pen and ink.</decoNote>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="129r" to="138v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tashbets</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תשב"ץ</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/8698827">Samson ben Zadok</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/8698827">שמשון בן צדוק</persName>
							</author>
							<filiation>Cf. also Add 18424 <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">538</ref> and 18685 <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">513</ref>.</filiation>
							<note>
								<p>The index, between folios 129r-130r, contains 497 positions. The paragraphs within the text are in almost entire disagreement with this enumeration.</p>
								<p>Liḳute ha-Ram begin on folio 137v.</p>
								<p>The elements which are absent from this recension of the text in comparison to the printed editions are provided in the marginal notes.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="138v" to="152v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perushim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פירושים</title>
							<note>
								<p>Comments on the passages of Bava metsi῾a, Bava ḳama, Giṭin and Sanhedrin. </p>
								<p>Contains a number of responses of <name type="person" role="author">Meir of Rothenburg</name> and others, on the same subjects. </p>
								<p>Imperfect at the end.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>152 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>330</height>
										<width>250</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>240/260</height>
										<width>170/200</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>152 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>19 quires of 8 leaves each, marked by catchwords at the end.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>First and last leaves slightly damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="36 63" writtenLines="35 62">
									<p>Visible pricking and plummet ruling.</p>
									<p>Hair-side and flesh-side of the folios indistinguishable.</p>
									<p>Last line written within ruling.</p>
									<p>Chapter initials given in larger characters. </p>
									<p>Catchwords in pen and ink designs (e.g. 112v, 120v).</p>
									<p>Ornamented tails of letters in the last line of text.</p>
									<p>Preserves original Hebrew foliation in the upper left-hand corner of each recto, beginning with 352 and finishing with 502 (which must have been extended over a large number of volumes). The first 128 folios bear also numbers 1-128 in the middle of the upper margin.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Ashkenazi semi-cursive script of the 14th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="128v"/> and <locus from="129r" to="152v"/> due to two different but contemporary hands.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>A strip of vellum of Tefilin shel rosh with the inscribed text of Ex. 13:1-10, pasted on folio [153]. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Zeraḥ ben Shemu'el Kats</name> of <name type="place">Padua</name>: inscribed with a date <date calendar="Hebrew">5404 </date>(<date calendar="Gregorian">1644</date>), folio <locus n="124v"/>.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
